^  The same story, however, asserts that Thales emigrated to Miletus; and that he did not become a student of nature until after his political career.
This story has to be rejected if one is to believe that Thales was a native of Miletus, and other typical things about him like his prediction of the eclipse.
^  The aphorism has also been attributed to various other philosophers.
