===Direct proof===
{{Main|Direct proof}}

In direct proof, the conclusion is established by logically combining the axioms, definitions, and earlier theorems.<ref>Cupillari, p.
20.</ref> For example, direct proof can be used to prove that the sum of two ] ]s is always even:

:Consider two even integers ''x'' and ''y''.
